HSC Survey Results

German Bank Survey # 7 Results from 03/11/2024

Survey Details

3 commercial purse seiners conducted this fishing survey on 03/11/2024 starting at 18:00:00.

The Morning Star was able to complete two transects each in the German Bank and Seal Island Box. The Lady Melissa completed two transects in each the German Bank and Seal Island Box, but was unable to record for the two transects in the German Bank box by an unknown cause. The Brunswick Provider completed two transects in the German Bank box and did not complete their transects in the Seal Island box..

There was a plankton tow and replicate conducted and CTD cast by Lady Melissa.

No tags were applied during this survey.

Since no fish were caught, no samples were obtained for target strength estimation.

Acoustic Equipment

Each vessel was equipped with a Simrad ES38-18/200-18C combi (2-in-1) transducer prior to the survey that contains a 38kHz split beam and 200 kHz single beam transducer. Data was logged to the computer hard-drive for post-processing. All participating boats were calibrated on 38kHz before the survey.

Survey Results

Main Results

The results are subject to change as DFO will re-evaluate data editing, area estimation and apply a target strength.

Preliminary biomass prediction for German Bank using standardized parallel transects is 2,886mt, and with turnover applied 1,811mt. The preliminary biomass estimate for Seal Island is 1,134mt.

Vessel Performance

Speed

Average vessel speed was 9.09. This is above the 8 knot requirement; vessels are urged to slow down to prevent backscatter noise from interfering with the acoustic data.

The speed for each transect are rudimentary and are calculated based on distance. If a significant amount of distance is cut, the speed will appear slower.

Distance

More than 2km of distance was cut from the planned lines; vessels are reminded to complete their assigned lines straight and without deviating or cutting corners short.
